SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1138
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor the Greeneville-Greene County Public
Library on fifty years at its current location.
WHEREAS, Tennessee's public libraries have long been committed to providing citizens
with the necessary resources for growth and prosperity in modern society; and
WHEREAS, no public library is more committed to this mission than the Greeneville-
Greene County Public Library, which marked fifty years at its current location at 210 N. Main
Street in November 2025; and
WHEREAS, the Greeneville-Greene County library was established in 1908 and was
housed at the Carnegie Library on Summer Street from 1915 to 1975; and
WHEREAS, as the library outgrew this space and the building needed significant repairs,
the site for a new library was identified, with the cost of the project coming in at $360,000; and
WHEREAS, in "the biggest fundraising drive in the county's history" at the time, Greene
County residents raised nearly half of the necessary funds, or $140,000, during an eighteen-
month period; and
WHEREAS, in October and November of 1975, teams of volunteers and a local Girl
Scout troop carried the entire collection of books by hand from the old library to the new facility
on Main Street; and
WHEREAS, the library opened November 9, 1975, in a 10,000-square-foot building that
was quadruple the size of the old Carnegie library; and
WHEREAS, this safe and welcoming public space continues to be a vital resource for
the community by providing internet access, public computers, and office services in addition to
traditional printed materials; and
SJR1138
017651
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the Greeneville-Greene County library is an important place for learning and
discovery among those who are curious about the world in which they live and its many different
philosophies, cultures, and adventures; and
WHEREAS, the staff and patrons of the Greeneville-Greene County library are worthy of
our approbation on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the Greeneville-Greene County Public
Library on the occasion of celebrating fifty years at its current location, as we commend its
ongoing commitment to growth and discovery through print and digital materials.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
